Hemorrhagic Fever
Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic]
'0.831100','15.441667',5,12503
Suspected Acute Haemorrhagic Fever in the Republic of the Congo
u" The three deaths were among male forest hunters from Mokouangonda who presented similar symptoms of epistaxis (nose bleeds), bloody diarrhoea, cough and fever prior to deaths after a 1-2 week long hunting expedition in the Odzala National Park. A joint Ministry of Health (MoH) and WHO team is currently in the field to assess the situation and to collect clinical samples for diagnosis. These will be tested by the Centre International de Recherches M\xe9dicales de Franceville (CIRMF) Gabon, and Institut National de Recherche Biom\xe9dicale \xe0 Kinshasa, DRC.  A Regional Coordination Committee to contain the outbreak has been established in Ouesso, Sangha Region, under the Direction G\xe9n\xe9rale de la Sant\xe9, assisted by WHO and other international partners including Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS) in Congo and Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle in France. Measures to respond to the disease outbreak including epidemiological investigation, social mobilization and infection control are being implemented in the area.  ", 'Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic] | Hemorrhagic Fever | Humans'
http://www.who.int/entity/csr/don/2010_06_29/en/index.html

HM Community News Reports
29 Jun 2010
Undiagnosed
Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic]
'0.831100','15.441667',5,12503
ReliefWeb \u00bb Document \u00bb Suspected Acute Haemorrhagic Fever in the ...
u" Suspected Acute Haemorrhagic Fever in the Republic of the Congo \n29 June 2010 -- WHO has received preliminary reports of five suspected cases, including three deaths, with acute haemorrhagic fever from Mokouangonda, an isolated forest village of about 100 inhabitants in Mokoke district, Region of Sangha, in northern Republic of the Congo (Brazzaville).\n The three deaths were among male forest hunters from Mokouangonda who presented similar symptoms of epistaxis (nose bleeds), bloody diarrhoea, cough and fever prior to deaths after a 1-2 week long hunting expedition in the Odzala National Park.\n A joint Ministry of Health (MoH) and WHO team is currently in the field to assess the situation and to collect clinical samples for diagnosis. These will be tested by the Centre International de Recherches M\xc3\xa9dicales de Franceville (CIRMF) Gabon, and Institut National de Recherche Biom\xc3\xa9dicale \xc3\xa0 Kinshasa, DRC.\n A Regional Coordination Committee to contain the outbreak has been established in Ouesso, Sangha Region, under the Direction G\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rale de la Sant\xc3\xa9, assisted by WHO and other international partners including Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS) in Congo and Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle in France. Measures to respond to the disease outbreak including epidemiological investigation, social mobilization and infection control are being implemented in the area. ", 'Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic] | Undiagnosed | Humans', 'Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic] | Hemorrhagic Fever | Humans'
http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/rwb.nsf/db900SID/EGUA-86VMGC?OpenDocument

29 Jun 2010
Hemorrhagic Fever
Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic]
'0.831100','15.441667',5,12503
ReliefWeb \u00bb Document \u00bb Suspected Acute Haemorrhagic Fever in the ...
u" Suspected Acute Haemorrhagic Fever in the Republic of the Congo \n29 June 2010 -- WHO has received preliminary reports of five suspected cases, including three deaths, with acute haemorrhagic fever from Mokouangonda, an isolated forest village of about 100 inhabitants in Mokoke district, Region of Sangha, in northern Republic of the Congo (Brazzaville).\n The three deaths were among male forest hunters from Mokouangonda who presented similar symptoms of epistaxis (nose bleeds), bloody diarrhoea, cough and fever prior to deaths after a 1-2 week long hunting expedition in the Odzala National Park.\n A joint Ministry of Health (MoH) and WHO team is currently in the field to assess the situation and to collect clinical samples for diagnosis. These will be tested by the Centre International de Recherches M\xc3\xa9dicales de Franceville (CIRMF) Gabon, and Institut National de Recherche Biom\xc3\xa9dicale \xc3\xa0 Kinshasa, DRC.\n A Regional Coordination Committee to contain the outbreak has been established in Ouesso, Sangha Region, under the Direction G\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9rale de la Sant\xc3\xa9, assisted by WHO and other international partners including Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS) in Congo and Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle in France. Measures to respond to the disease outbreak including epidemiological investigation, social mobilization and infection control are being implemented in the area. ", 'Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic] | Undiagnosed | Humans', 'Mokouangonda, Mokote District, Region de la Sangha, Congo [Republic] | Hemorrhagic Fever | Humans'

asankusu: quatorze personnes meurent d\u2019une maladie inconnue \u00e0 Songo
u'Une maladie non encore identifi\xc3\xa9e s\xc3\xa9vit depuis le d\xc3\xa9but de semaine \xc3\xa0 Songo, localit\xc3\xa9 situ\xc3\xa9e \xc3\xa0 12 kilom\xc3\xa8tres de la cit\xc3\xa9 de Basankusu, dans le district de l\xe2\x80\x99Equateur. Une quinzaine de personnes en sont mortes et on enregistre dix malades, selon le m\xc3\xa9decin chef du district sanitaire de l\xe2\x80\x99Equateur. Mais pour des raisons li\xc3\xa9es \xc3\xa0 la d\xc3\xa9ontologie, ce m\xc3\xa9decin se refuse \xc3\xa0 ce stade \xc3\xa0 tout commentaire.\nLe commissaire du district de l\xe2\x80\x99Equateur, Boniface Awenze, affirme que des \xc3\xa9quipes m\xc3\xa9dicales ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 d\xc3\xa9p\xc3\xaach\xc3\xa9es sur les lieux pour s\xe2\x80\x99enqu\xc3\xa9rir de la situation. La m\xc3\xaame source indique que la maladie se manifeste par les maux de t\xc3\xaate, la diarrh\xc3\xa9e, la colique abdominale et la fi\xc3\xa8vre. Il l\xe2\x80\x99a dit jeudi \xc3\xa0 Radio Okapi :\n\xc2\xabSelon les statistiques, nous avons quatorze d\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa8s et six malades. Parmi ces six malades, il y a deux enfants hospitalis\xc3\xa9s, et les quatre adultes qui ont fui l\xe2\x80\x99h\xc3\xb4pital vers des \xc3\xa9glises \xc2\xbb\nD\xe2\x80\x99apr\xc3\xa8s le commissaire de district, les personnes d\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9d\xc3\xa9es pr\xc3\xa9sentaient tous les signes de cette maladie non encore identifi\xc3\xa9e. Il poursuit :\n\xc2\xab Nous avons d\xc3\xa9velopp\xc3\xa9 deux pistes. Il y a une piste judiciaire parce que des soup\xc3\xa7ons p\xc3\xa8sent sur des personnes qui auraient utilis\xc3\xa9 la sorcellerie [pour tuer les victimes]. De l\xe2\x80\x99autre c\xc3\xb4t\xc3\xa9, nous avons mobilis\xc3\xa9 une \xc3\xa9quipe m\xc3\xa9dicale compos\xc3\xa9e du m\xc3\xa9decin chef de zone de sant\xc3\xa9 et des infirmiers. Cette \xc3\xa9quipe est d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 sur le terrain pour mener des investigations m\xc3\xa9dicales et voir s\xe2\x80\x99il s\xe2\x80\x99agit d\xe2\x80\x99une \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie.\xc2\xbb\nEn attendant des solutions appropri\xc3\xa9es, Boniface Awenze demande \xc3\xa0 la population d\xe2\x80\x99observer les conseils de l\xe2\x80\x99\xc3\xa9quipe m\xc3\xa9dicale d\xc3\xa9ploy\xc3\xa9e sur le terrain et d\xe2\x80\x99\xc3\xa9viter l\xe2\x80\x99expansion de cette maladie dans d\xe2\x80\x99autres localit\xc3\xa9s. Surge in rabies cases
u'Panchkula, June 28\nWith a rise in the dog bite cases in city and its periphery, there has been a substantial increase in the number of rabies patients in the recent past.\n\nAccording to sources, five to six rabies patients visit the General Hospital, Sector 6, everyday.\n\nMore than 100 cases of dog bite were reported at the hospital in May. Come monsoon and the number may swell, say experts.\n\nSources said most of the patients came from rural areas, urban slums or the adjoining towns such as Dhakoli, Zirakpur and Baltana.\n\nDog or monkey bite cases were also reported from Madna, Morni, Berwala, Nadda, Kalka, Raipur Rani and Barwala.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cDeforestation has forced monkeys and other dangerous species to stray into these areas,\xe2\x80\x9d said sources.\n\nA monkey bite can also cause rabies -- a disease caused by the lyssa virus, which has the tendency of hiding itself from the immune system and not giving the body time to respond to its attack. The immune system\xe2\x80\x99s inability to combat the virus allows it to reach the central nervous system.\n\nHere, it replicates quickly and spreads all over the brain, causing inflammation and affecting its functioning. Only a vaccine can prevent this from happening. An affected person develops hydrophobia, becomes anxious and hyperactive. There is increasingly uncontrolled movement, confusion and delirium. At this stage, animals also go mad and bite. ', 'Panchkula, Chandigarh, India | Rabies | Humans'

Health advisory issued for water contact at Sunset Bay State Park ...
'A public health advisory was issued Wednesday due to higher-than-normal levels of bacteria in ocean waters\nat Sunset Bay State Park Beach in Coos County.\nIncreased pathogen and fecal bacteria levels in ocean waters can come from both shore and inland sources\nsuch as storm water runoff, sewer overflows, failing septic systems and even animal waste from livestock,\npets and wildlife.\nWater samples indicate higher-than-normal levels of fecal bacteria, which can result in gastroenteritis, skin\nrashes, upper respiratory infections and other illnesses. Direct contact with the water should be avoided until\nthe advisories are lifted, especially for children and the elderly, who may be more vulnerable to waterborne\nbacteria.\nWhile these advisories are in effect at Sunset Bay State Park Beach, visitors should avoid wading in nearby\ncreeks or in discolored water, and stay clear of water runoff flowing into the ocean. Even if there is no advisory\nin effect, officials recommend avoiding swimming in the ocean within 48 hours after a rainstorm.\nState officials advise that the status of water contact advisories at beaches is subject to change. For the most\nrecent information on advisories, please visit www.oregon.gov/DHS/ph/beaches/index.shtml or call 877-290-\n6767.\n ', 'Sunset Bay State Park, Oregon, United States | Waterborne Illness | Humans'

Sant\u00e9: Eviter une nouvelle \u00e9pid\u00e9mie de dengue au Cap-Vert
u' Actualit\xc3\xa9s africaines: Economie Politique Finances Sports \n Sant\xc3\xa9: Eviter une nouvelle \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de dengue au Cap-Vert \nPraia, Cap-Vert - Le gouvernement capverdien a d\xc3\xa9cid\xc3\xa9 de tol\xc3\xa9rer les absences, ce vendredi, des fonctionnaires ainsi que des travailleurs du secteur priv\xc3\xa9, pour leur permettre de participer \xc3\xa0 la campagne nationale de salubrit\xc3\xa9, visant \xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9liminer les foyers de moustiques afin de pr\xc3\xa9venir l\'apparition d\'une nouvelle \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de dengue dans l\'archipel, a appris la PANA \xc3\xa0 Praia de source officielle. \n En 2009, le Cap-Vert avait enregistr\xc3\xa9 pour la premi\xc3\xa8re fois, une \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de dengue qui avait fait quatre morts sur un total de 21.304 cas. D\'apr\xc3\xa8s les statistiques recueillies par les autorit\xc3\xa9s sanitaires, cette ann\xc3\xa9e, 305 cas de dengue ont d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 notifi\xc3\xa9s, surtout dans les \xc3\xaeles de Fogo (161) et Santiago (115), sans cas h\xc3\xa9morragique de la maladie ni victime mortelle. En annon\xc3\xa7ant le lancement de cette campagne de nettoyage, le ministre capverdien de la Sant\xc3\xa9, Basilio Ramos, a r\xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9 qu\'apr\xc3\xa8s la r\xc3\xa9alisation de deux \xc3\xa9tudes \xc3\xa9tymologiques pour \xc3\xa9valuer les niveaux d\'infestation, l\'on a constat\xc3\xa9 que l\'assainissement du pays "laissait \xc3\xa0 d\xc3\xa9sirer", d\'o\xc3\xb9 la volont\xc3\xa9 du gouvernement de renforcer les actions de pr\xc3\xa9vention du risque. Dans ce cadre, le gouvernement, pour \xc3\xa9viter que la situation de l\'an dernier ne se r\xc3\xa9p\xc3\xa8te, m\xc3\xa8ne, depuis le d\xc3\xa9but de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e, des actions de sensibilisation aupr\xc3\xa8s des populations et de d\xc3\xa9sinfestation. Lundi prochain, commencera une autre campagne qui vise \xc3\xa0 pulv\xc3\xa9riser des structures collectives et les maisons des \xc3\xaeles \xc3\xa0 grand risque, notamment Santiago, Fogo et Maio. En plus de la dengue, les structures sanitaires de l\'archipel sont aussi en \xc3\xa9tat d\'alerte pour ce qui est de la fi\xc3\xa8vre jaune, maladie \xc3\xa9radiqu\xc3\xa9e depuis plusieurs ann\xc3\xa9es, mais qui peut r\xc3\xa9appara\xc3\xaetre parce qu\'au Cap-Vert, on d\xc3\xa9nombre le moustique vecteur de cette maladie du fait des relations qui existent avec les pays o\xc3\xb9 la maladie est notifi\xc3\xa9e. La campagne de ce vendredi, baptis\xc3\xa9e "Nettoyer le Cap-Vert", sera coordonn\xc3\xa9e par les mairies de chaque arrondissement, toutefois, le gouvernement esp\xc3\xa8re l\'implication de toute la population, vu le risque d\'apparition des maladies transmises par les moustiques, telles que la dengue, la fi\xc3\xa8vre jaune et le paludisme, si l\'on n\'am\xc3\xa9liore pas l\'assainissement du pays. Le ministre de la Sant\xc3\xa9 a garanti, cependant, que contrairement \xc3\xa0 l\'an dernier, o\xc3\xb9 les autorit\xc3\xa9s sanitaires ne savaient pas comment r\xc3\xa9agir face \xc3\xa0 la dengue, le Cap-Vert est maintenant pr\xc3\xa9par\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 affronter toute apparition de la maladie. "Nous avons un plan de contingence et les structures de sant\xc3\xa9 suivront ce qui est d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 pr\xc3\xa9vu et nous travaillons pour que la situation ne se r\xc3\xa9p\xc3\xa8te pas", a pr\xc3\xa9cis\xc3\xa9 Basilio Ramos, avis\xc3\xa9 que le plus grand enjeu pour \xc3\xa9viter une nouvelle \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie "sera toujours la pr\xc3\xa9vention". Praia - Pana 26/06/2010\n RESULTATS COUPE DU MONDE FOOTBALL 2010 AFRIQUE DU SUD  ', 'Cape Verde | Dengue | Humans', 'Santiago, Cape Verde | Dengue | Humans', 'Ilha do Fogo, Cape Verde | Dengue | Humans'
http://www.afriquejet.com/afrique-de-l%27ouest/cap%11vert/sante:-eviter-une-nouvelle-epidemie-de-dengue-au-cap-vert-2010062651785.html

u' Actualit\xc3\xa9s africaines: Economie Politique Finances Sports \n Sant\xc3\xa9: Eviter une nouvelle \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de dengue au Cap-Vert \nPraia, Cap-Vert - Le gouvernement capverdien a d\xc3\xa9cid\xc3\xa9 de tol\xc3\xa9rer les absences, ce vendredi, des fonctionnaires ainsi que des travailleurs du secteur priv\xc3\xa9, pour leur permettre de participer \xc3\xa0 la campagne nationale de salubrit\xc3\xa9, visant \xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9liminer les foyers de moustiques afin de pr\xc3\xa9venir l\'apparition d\'une nouvelle \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de dengue dans l\'archipel, a appris la PANA \xc3\xa0 Praia de source officielle. \n En 2009, le Cap-Vert avait enregistr\xc3\xa9 pour la premi\xc3\xa8re fois, une \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de dengue qui avait fait quatre morts sur un total de 21.304 cas. D\'apr\xc3\xa8s les statistiques recueillies par les autorit\xc3\xa9s sanitaires, cette ann\xc3\xa9e, 305 cas de dengue ont d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 notifi\xc3\xa9s, surtout dans les \xc3\xaeles de Fogo (161) et Santiago (115), sans cas h\xc3\xa9morragique de la maladie ni victime mortelle. En annon\xc3\xa7ant le lancement de cette campagne de nettoyage, le ministre capverdien de la Sant\xc3\xa9, Basilio Ramos, a r\xc3\xa9v\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9 qu\'apr\xc3\xa8s la r\xc3\xa9alisation de deux \xc3\xa9tudes \xc3\xa9tymologiques pour \xc3\xa9valuer les niveaux d\'infestation, l\'on a constat\xc3\xa9 que l\'assainissement du pays "laissait \xc3\xa0 d\xc3\xa9sirer", d\'o\xc3\xb9 la volont\xc3\xa9 du gouvernement de renforcer les actions de pr\xc3\xa9vention du risque. Dans ce cadre, le gouvernement, pour \xc3\xa9viter que la situation de l\'an dernier ne se r\xc3\xa9p\xc3\xa8te, m\xc3\xa8ne, depuis le d\xc3\xa9but de l\'ann\xc3\xa9e, des actions de sensibilisation aupr\xc3\xa8s des populations et de d\xc3\xa9sinfestation. Lundi prochain, commencera une autre campagne qui vise \xc3\xa0 pulv\xc3\xa9riser des structures collectives et les maisons des \xc3\xaeles \xc3\xa0 grand risque, notamment Santiago, Fogo et Maio. En plus de la dengue, les structures sanitaires de l\'archipel sont aussi en \xc3\xa9tat d\'alerte pour ce qui est de la fi\xc3\xa8vre jaune, maladie \xc3\xa9radiqu\xc3\xa9e depuis plusieurs ann\xc3\xa9es, mais qui peut r\xc3\xa9appara\xc3\xaetre parce qu\'au Cap-Vert, on d\xc3\xa9nombre le moustique vecteur de cette maladie du fait des relations qui existent avec les pays o\xc3\xb9 la maladie est notifi\xc3\xa9e. La campagne de ce vendredi, baptis\xc3\xa9e "Nettoyer le Cap-Vert", sera coordonn\xc3\xa9e par les mairies de chaque arrondissement, toutefois, le gouvernement esp\xc3\xa8re l\'implication de toute la population, vu le risque d\'apparition des maladies transmises par les moustiques, telles que la dengue, la fi\xc3\xa8vre jaune et le paludisme, si l\'on n\'am\xc3\xa9liore pas l\'assainissement du pays. Le ministre de la Sant\xc3\xa9 a garanti, cependant, que contrairement \xc3\xa0 l\'an dernier, o\xc3\xb9 les autorit\xc3\xa9s sanitaires ne savaient pas comment r\xc3\xa9agir face \xc3\xa0 la dengue, le Cap-Vert est maintenant pr\xc3\xa9par\xc3\xa9 \xc3\xa0 affronter toute apparition de la maladie. "Nous avons un plan de contingence et les structures de sant\xc3\xa9 suivront ce qui est d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 pr\xc3\xa9vu et nous travaillons pour que la situation ne se r\xc3\xa9p\xc3\xa8te pas", a pr\xc3\xa9cis\xc3\xa9 Basilio Ramos, avis\xc3\xa9 que le plus grand enjeu pour \xc3\xa9viter une nouvelle \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie "sera toujours la pr\xc3\xa9vention". Praia - Pana 26/06/2010\n RESULTATS COUPE DU MONDE FOOTBALL 2010 AFRIQUE DU SUD  ', 'Cape Verde | Dengue | Humans', 'Santiago, Cape Verde | Dengue | Humans', 'Ilha do Fogo, Cape Verde | Dengue | Humans'

Cameroun : 23 morts dans une \u00e9pid\u00e9mie de chol\u00e9ra dans l'extr\u00eame-nord
u' \xa0\xa0 Le portail togolais par excellence ! \n \xa0\xa0 Annuaire t\xe9l\xe9phonique \n Une \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie de chol\xc3\xa9ra survenue dans la r\xc3\xa9gion de l\'extr\xc3\xaame-nord du Cameroun a fait 23 morts parmi 140 malades d\xc3\xa9clar\xc3\xa9s, a fait savoir le ministre camerounais de la Sant\xc3\xa9 publique, Andr\xc3\xa9 Mama Fouda, dans une d\xc3\xa9claration publi\xc3\xa9e jeudi soir \xc3\xa0 Yaound\xc3\xa9. \n \xa0 Observ\xc3\xa9e "depuis quelques semaines" dans 7 districts de sant\xc3\xa9 ( Mogod\xc3\xa9, Kousseri, Mada, Makari, M\xc3\xa9ri, Koza et Gu\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9), cette \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie est "favoris\xc3\xa9e par la survenue des pluies. A la date du 21 juin 2010, 140 cas ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 notifi\xc3\xa9s, 23 d\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa8s enregistr\xc3\xa9s, soit un taux de l\xc3\xa9talit\xc3\xa9 de 16%", a-t-il pr\xc3\xa9cis\xc3\xa9. Comme mesures d\'urgence, le minist\xc3\xa8re de la Sant\xc3\xa9 publique a annonc\xc3\xa9 la mise \xc3\xa0 disposition des m\xc3\xa9dicaments et des produits de traitement d\'eau. Appelant les populations \xc3\xa0 la vigilance sanitaire, il recommande, en vue de circonscrire l\'\xc3\xa9volution de l\' \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mie, de saisir rapidement la formation sanitaire la plus proche pour tout cas suspect et le respect des pr\xc3\xa9cautions minimales d\'hygi\xc3\xa8ne. Il s\'agit d\'\xc3\xa9viter de d\xc3\xa9f\xc3\xa9quer en plein air ou dans les cours d\' eau, en utilisant les latrines ou les fosses perdues, de bien bouillir l\'eau avant son utilisation, de cuire suffisamment les aliments, et de se laver les mains apr\xc3\xa8s chaque selle et avant les repas. Le ministre Mama Fouda a entrepris une visite dans la r\xc3\xa9gion afin de mieux appr\xc3\xa9hender l\'ampleur et l\'impact de la maladie. L\'extr\xc3\xaame-nord du Cameroun est une r\xc3\xa9gion r\xc3\xa9guli\xc3\xa8rement affect\xc3\xa9e par des \xc3\xa9pid\xc3\xa9mies mortelles de chol\xc3\xa9ra, dont la derni\xc3\xa8re remonte au mois de janvier. \n Pour faire des surprises \xc3\xa0 vos parents et amis, iciLome a pens\xe9 \xc3\xa0 vous. Although most types are harmless and live in the intestines of healthy humans and animals, the O157 type produces a powerful toxin that can cause severe illness. PRO\/EAFR> Viral conjunctivitis - Uganda (02): (Kampala, Hoima) RFI

NEWS SCAN: Oil spill and food pathogens
'Oil spill may spur growth of oyster-contaminating bacteria\nThe massive oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico is likely to stimulate the growth of oil-consuming marine bacteria, possibly including pathogenic species that are sometimes found in oysters, according to a New York Times report. One pathogenic Vibrio species, V parahaemolyticus, has "a deep thirst for crude oil," says the report by Paul Voosen of the Greenwire news service. The species rarely causes serious illness, but another Vibrio species, V vulnificus, does cause serious illness, and experts suspect it, too, may be stimulated by the oil. Vibrio populations grow in the summer, and scientists say there is a good possibility that the spilled crude oil and the "organic flotsam" it leaves behind will further spur the growth of the bacteria. A US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) spokeswoman, Meghan Scott, said the FDA is aware of the Vibrio threat but believes the bacteria will decline as the oil is degraded. Most oyster reefs in the spill-affected area are currently closed, the report said. ', 'Gulf of Mexico | Environmental | Humans'

u" Updated\xa0Monday, June 14, 2010 9:52\xa0am\xa0TWN,\xa0The China Post news staff \n Woman dies from eating supplements she sells \n TAIPEI, Taiwan -- A woman working in direct sales died of what was diagnosed to be drug-induced acute hepatitis, after eating five types of health supplements she sold, the United Daily News reported yesterday. \n According to Chien Jung-nan, gastro-intestinal doctor at Chang Gung hospital's Keelung branch, the woman, 50, arrived at the hospital with liver failure, which resulted in her blood being unable to coagulate. The woman appeared yellow, with a liver index of 2,000 to 3,000, as opposed to 40 for regular people, Chien recalled. She died ten days afterwards, due to a lack of available livers for transplantation. The woman had no history of hepatitis B or C, yet for years, she had been eating health supplements she sold, one of which was lecithin, Chien said. The products might have acted upon one another to produce toxin, the doctor said. For hepatitis patients, they should eat medicine prescribed by doctors, rather than health supplements, Chien said. This is especially so for patients of chronic hepatitis B and C, he said. \n Taipei\xa0Breaking News  ", 'Taiwan | Hepatitis | Humans'

He added that another cause of the eating disorder would be overeating rice dumplings, because glutinous rice, also commonly known as sticky rice, takes longer and is more difficult to digest. Stewed pork, peanuts, and seafood, ingredients commonly seen in rice dumplings, are high in cholesterol, so eating too many of them may be damaging to one's health, the doctor continued. HM Community News Reports
8 Jun 2010
Poisoning
Minnesota, United States
'46.225399','-94.658302',5,354
Tainted cocaine sickens five, killing two of them, in Twin Cities ...
' Jobs with the Pioneer Press \nCocaine tainted with a potent veterinary medicine has caused neutropenia in as many as five Minnesota drug users, including two who died, the state health department reported Monday. \n Neutropenia is an erosion of the neutrophil blood cells, which protect the body from infection. The two drug users who died had this condition but also other health problems, the department reported.\n The diseases likely were caused by levamisole, an anti-worm medication for animals that can damage human blood cells and platelets. Levamisole is commonly used by illicit-drug manufacturers to dilute cocaine.\n The first U.S. cases of neutropenia linked to tainted cocaine were reported in 2008 in New Mexico. Cases since have been reported throughout the U.S.  ', 'Minnesota, United States | Poisoning | Humans', 'Minneapolis-St. Paul-Bloomington, Minnesota, United States | Poisoning | Humans'

La d\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa9gation territoriale de l'ARS du Tarn en lien avec la sant\xc3\xa9 scolaire a fait un boulot magistral \xc2\xbb confie le Dr Charles Hemery de la cellule de veille et de gestion sanitaire de l'ARS. 35 personnes ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 recens\xc3\xa9es et 31 d'entre elles avaient d\xc3\xa9j\xc3\xa0 commenc\xc3\xa9 le traitement d\xc3\xa8s hier. \xc2\xab On a pu tr\xc3\xa8s vite lister avec le malade lui-m\xc3\xaame un certain nombre de personnes qui avaient \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 en contact rapproch\xc3\xa9, c'est-\xc3\xa0-dire au moins une heure \xc3\xa0 ses c\xc3\xb4t\xc3\xa9s, dans les dix derniers jours avant que la maladie ne se d\xc3\xa9clare \xc2\xbb, continue le Dr Hemery pr\xc3\xa9cisant que les 4 membres de la famille ont tout de suite \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 trait\xc3\xa9s. \n17 coll\xc3\xa9giens concern\xc3\xa9s \n\xc3\x80 commencer par ces camarades de classe de 3e du coll\xc3\xa8ge de Lacaune o\xc3\xb9 il est scolaris\xc3\xa9. \xc2\xab On a rapidement \xc3\xa9tabli une liste \xc2\xbb, raconte la principale de l'\xc3\xa9tablissement Brigitte H\xc3\xa9ral, pr\xc3\xa9venu mercredi soir, et qui a parfaitement g\xc3\xa9r\xc3\xa9 la situation avec le m\xc3\xa9decin scolaire le Dr Badouraly. 17 \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa8ves ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 recens\xc3\xa9s et ont pu dans la journ\xc3\xa9e se faire prescrire par leur m\xc3\xa9decin traitant l'antibiotique \xc3\xa0 aller chercher dans les 2 pharmacies lacaunaises qui ont rapidement \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 dot\xc3\xa9es du m\xc3\xa9dicament. Le traitement est \xc3\xa0 prendre durant 48 heures. \xc2\xab On a aussi fait une information \xc3\xa0 tous les \xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa8ves, au personnel enseignant et administratif et on a \xc3\xa9crit une lettre \xc3\xa0 tous les parents pour les rassurer \xc2\xbb, ajoute la principale qui pr\xc3\xa9cise que la vie du coll\xc3\xa8ge n'a pas \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 perturb\xc3\xa9e. \xc2\xab En effet, il n'y a aucun risque d'attraper cette bact\xc3\xa9rie simplement en croisant l'\xc3\xa9l\xc3\xa8ve. La contamination se fait par des petites gouttes de salive \xc2\xbb, explique le Dr H\xc3\xa9mery. u' Sofort wechseln zu: Seiteninhalt \n Malawi 2010: Wie hier im Distrikt Blantyre werden zurzeit in Malawi Hunderttausende Kinder geimpft. \nImpfung von 2, 5 Millionen Kindern nach Masernausbruch - 8.000 Patienten sind in Behandlung \n Seit Februar 2010 steht Malawi der gr\xc3\xb6\xc3\x9ften Masernepidemie seit 13 Jahren gegen\xc3\xbcber. Zusammen mit den Gesundheitsbeh\xc3\xb6rden des Landes behandeln Mitarbeiter von \xc3\x84rzte ohne Grenzen betroffene Patienten und f\xc3\xbchren Impfungen f\xc3\xbcr mehr als 2,5 Millionen Kinder durch. Um diese schwerwiegende Epidemie zu beenden, die viele Menschenleben bedroht, werden aber gr\xc3\xb6\xc3\x9fere Anstrengungen auf nationaler und internationaler Ebene n\xc3\xb6tig sein. Masern geh\xc3\xb6ren weltweit zu den h\xc3\xa4ufigsten Ursachen von Todesf\xc3\xa4llen bei Kindern und Erwachsenen. Die Krankheit kann schwerwiegende Nebenwirkungen haben und das Risiko erh\xc3\xb6hen, an Mangelern\xc3\xa4hrung zu erkranken. \nOffiziellen malawischen Angaben zufolge sind bislang mehr als 9.000 Menschen an Masern  ', 'Malawi | Measles | Humans'

Shrimp Recall: June 5, 2010
'Allergy Alert: Eastern Fish Co. (Teaneck, NJ) recalls certain date codes of Bloom brand and Hannaford brand frozen raw extra jumbo shrimp because the product may contain undeclared sulfites. The recall applies to shrimp sold in 16-ounce packages and at full-service seafood cases. The recall was initiated after Bloom was notified by the North Carolina Department of Agriculture that test results from routine product sampling indicated the presence of sulfites in the shrimp. The recalled products were distributed to Hannaford stores and to independent stores serviced by Hannaford in New York, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, Vermont and Maine, and to Bloom stores in North Carolina, South Carolina, Virginia and Maryland. Un coll\u00e9gien victime d'une m\u00e9ningite
u" Publi\xc3\xa9 le 03/06/2010 03:52 | Br. M. \nUn adolescent de quinze ans, habitant Lacaune, a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 hospitalis\xc3\xa9 hier au centre hospitalier de Castres-Mazamet pour une probable infection invasive \xc3\xa0 m\xc3\xa9ningocoque, plus commun\xc3\xa9ment appel\xc3\xa9e m\xc3\xa9ningite. Son \xc3\xa9tat de sant\xc3\xa9 est satisfaisant selon les m\xc3\xa9decins. Mais l'Agence r\xc3\xa9gionale de sant\xc3\xa9 de Midi-Pyr\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9es cherche aujourd'hui \xc3\xa0 joindre toutes les personnes \xc2\xab qui ont eu un contact \xc3\xa9troit et prolong\xc3\xa9 avec lui pendant les jours pr\xc3\xa9c\xc3\xa9dents \xc2\xbb. Les personnes concern\xc3\xa9es et sa famille recevront en effet un traitement pr\xc3\xa9ventif pour la m\xc3\xa9ningite par \xc2\xab la mise en place de la chimioprophylaxie \xc2\xbb. Le coll\xc3\xa8ge du Montalet \xc3\xa0 Lacaune, o\xc3\xb9 est scolaris\xc3\xa9 le jeune homme, a \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 pr\xc3\xa9venu hier soir afin de prendre toutes les dispositions n\xc3\xa9cessaires. Le service de la sant\xc3\xa9 scolaire de l'\xc3\xa9tablissement prendra en charge aujourd'hui les camarades de classes de l'adolescent ainsi que le personnel enseignant et administratif qui auraient \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 en contact avec lui. \nLe pr\xc3\xa9sident du club de rugby o\xc3\xb9 le jeune homme \xc3\xa9tait licenci\xc3\xa9 a \xc3\xa9galement \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 pr\xc3\xa9venu hier en fin d'apr\xc3\xa8s-midi. \xc2\xab L'Agence r\xc3\xa9gionale de sant\xc3\xa9 m'a demand\xc3\xa9 de fournir la liste des jeunes et de toutes les personnes qui ont \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 en contact avec lui lors des entra\xc3\xaenements de mercredi et samedi dernier auxquels il a particip\xc3\xa9. The Associated Press: Gulf spill workers complaining of flulike ...
u'\u2013\n 6 hours ago \nIn the past week, 11 workers who have been out on the water cleaning up oil from BP\'s blown-out well have been treated for what Dietrich calls "a pattern of symptoms" that could have been caused by the burning of crude oil, noxious fumes from the oil or the dispersants dumped in the Gulf to break it up. All workers were treated and released. \n"One person comes in, it could be multiple things," he said. ABC Radio Australia News:Stories:Death toll rises from PNG cholera ...
' Death toll rises from PNG cholera epidemic \n The cholera outbreak is getting worse at Hanuabada village in the centre of Port Moresby. [Radio Australia: Firmin Nanol] \nThe cholera epidemic in Papua New Guinea\'s capital, Port Moresby, is getting worse. At least seven people have died and there are now said to be as many as 600 suspected cases that have been detected since August, in coastal villages around Port Moresby. Last month, PNG\'s Health Minister declared a public health emergency in the capital, and at the time, there were media reports that funds to fight the epidemic had dried up. A Health Specialist with the Secretariat of the Pacific Community in PNG, David Thomson, says the problem is again, a lack of hygiene, clean water and poor sanitation. "In the urban areas you\'ve got a lot of settlement areas, low income settlement areas and also enclaves of squatter settlements and these are generally not well serviced with good quality water and sanitation standards and so forth are quite low, so diseases like cholera can certainly spread very quickly in that type of environment." \n Interact \n ABC Online  ', 'Port Moresby, National Capital, Papua New Guinea | Cholera | Humans', 'Hanuabada, National Capital, Papua New Guinea | Cholera | Humans'

u'A stray cat that tested positive for rabies in Whitpain should serve as a red flag for pet owners.\n\nFor pets that have not received the rabies vaccination, exposure is essentially a death sentence, according to Dr. Shaun Johnson, a veterinarian at the North Penn Animal Hospital in Towamencin.\n\nJohnson said the viral disease, which affects the animal\xe2\x80\x99s neurological system, spreads quickly.\n\nFamilies with rabid pets are also at risk, according to Johnson.\n\nHe said people diagnosed with rabies rarely live without treatment.\n\nThe county Public Health Code and state law requires all cats and dogs 3 months of age and older must be vaccinated against the virus. BERNAMA - 14 New H1N1 Cases Detected Nationwide
' KUALA LUMPUR, June 3 (Bernama) -- Fourteen new Influenza A(H1N1) positive cases were reported over the past 24 hours nationwide, increasing the total number of cases thus far to 14,864 cases, said Director-general of Health Tan Sri Dr Mohd Ismail Merican.\n\nOne influenza-like illness (ILI) cluster case was also detected in the last 24 hours at SMK Jalan Bukit, Kajang, Selangor whereby one of the four patients were tested positive for A(H1N1).\n\n"There are 64 ILI active cluster cases throughout the country," he said in a statement here Thursday.\n\nDr Mohd Ismail said 540 ILI cases were being treated in hospitals throughout the country and from the total, 45 or 8.3 per cent were confirmed A(H1N1) positive cases.\n\nHe said currently four H1N1 cases were being treated at the Intensive Care Units (ICU) where all the patients had high risk factor but the number of deaths remains at 87.\n\nMore information on H1N1 can be obtained at http://www.moh.gov.my or http://h1n1.moh.gov.my or by calling the ministry\'s hotline at 03-88810200/0300. u"ST THOMAS, USVI -- Health Commissioner Julia Sheen on Wednesday said the Department of Health has confirmed the US Virgin Islands' first case of Dengue Fever.\n\nThe case was reported in the St Thomas-St John district and follow-up testing confirmed positive for the disease caused by the Aedes Aegypti mosquito, which is mostly found in the home, Sheen said.\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cIncreased rains can make certain areas near the home a haven for mosquito breeding and place individuals at risk for Dengue Fever,\xe2\x80\x9d Sheen said. \xe2\x80\x9cWe went through both the hurricane and rainy seasons last year without a positive case of Dengue being reported and with this confirmed case, we urge residents to be vigilant and help their communities and the Department of Health stop the spread of Dengue Fever by doing basic things.\xe2\x80\x9d  ", 'Saint Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands | Dengue | Humans'
